AMERICA’S ENVOY claimed “excellent progress” in negotiations ahead of the country’s planned exit from Afghanistan. But stickier talks await, between the Islamist militia and the Afghan government. A promising new vaccine may at last tackle typhoid fever, which claims 160,000 lives every year. And, we travel to Scotland and hop on the world’s shortest scheduled flight. Runtime: 19 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn